# 2277 - if else
# Read two ASCII characters and determine if they are the same
# Output: '1' (ASCII 49) if same, '0' (ASCII 48) if different

# Initialize memory [0] and [1] to 48 and 49 for lookup
[0]<48
[1]<49

# Read first character into A
A<I

# Read second character into B
B<I

# Strategy: Set mem[B] = 1, then check if mem[A] == 1
# First, clear a region of memory (not necessary if already 0)

# Set mem[B] = 1
[B]<1

# Check mem[A] - if it's 1, they're equal
C<[A]

# C is now 0 or 1
# Use lookup: mem[0]=48, mem[1]=49
D<[C]

# Output result
O<D

# Halt
Z<1
